<paragraph id="4D2DF06E6871922D415FAF7759F0BC39" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
<taxonomicName id="C11069C34863DC5ED6E88150D79B476E" LSID="878E533F-731E-5EA8-BD35-769F5D8D8ABE" authority="sensu lato" authorityName="sensu lato" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Beauveria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Beauveria bassiana" order="Hypocreales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="bassiana">Beauveria bassiana sensu lato</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="777F2C73FFD67A84A2DF8DF14007A88C" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="host">
<paragraph id="C1E49DA8B0864C37A8A90C20D481C6A9" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Hosts.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9823D2AA7A7FBEE83EE9E975AB93AEBC" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
Many insect orders, including 
<taxonomicName id="5C358333733BF6DC80FC03B502B4873A" authorityName="Vuillemin" authorityYear="1912" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Ophiocordycipitaceae" genus="Beauveria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="order">Coleoptera</taxonomicName>
(e.g. 
<taxonomicName id="4F96F94FAD331EA9950AD865E5A916C0" authorityName="Vuillemin" authorityYear="1912" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Ophiocordycipitaceae" genus="Beauveria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="superFamily" superFamily="Elateroidea">Elateroidea</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="F11EE7B0167898FF4F80E6F873D025AE" authorityName="Vuillemin" authorityYear="1912" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Ophiocordycipitaceae" genus="Beauveria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="superFamily" superFamily="Tenebrionoidea">Tenebrionoidea</taxonomicName>
spp., 
<bibRefCitation id="923FAF68CD082827888D00D07F3913F8" author="Humber, RA" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences, USA" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" publicationUrl="http://arsef.fpsnl.cornell.edu./" refId="B20" refString="Humber, RA, Hansen, KS, 2005. USDA-ARS Collection of Entomopathogenic Fungal Cultures (ARSEF), ARSEF-Index: Host by Fungus. http://arsef.fpsnl.cornell.edu./" title="USDA-ARS Collection of Entomopathogenic Fungal Cultures (ARSEF), ARSEF-Index: Host by Fungus." url="http://arsef.fpsnl.cornell.edu./" year="2005">Humber and Hansen 2005</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="2BBE11F26EA7C761C5E9F351F50C839C" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jip.2014.05.005" author="Reddy, GVP" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Invertebrate Pathology" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="43 - 49" refId="B70" refString="Reddy, GVP, Tangtrakulwanich, K, Wu, SH, Miller, JH, Ophus, VL, Prewett, J, Jaronski, ST, 2014. Evaluation of the effectiveness of entomopathogens for the management of wireworms (Coleoptera: Elateridae) on spring wheat. Journal of Invertebrate Pathology 120: 43 - 49, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jip.2014.05.005" title="Evaluation of the effectiveness of entomopathogens for the management of wireworms (Coleoptera: Elateridae) on spring wheat." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jip.2014.05.005" volume="120" year="2014">Reddy et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="02384FB5F60E7EA3F089E089E5E15804" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/s10343-017-0406-8" author="Sufyan, M" journalOrPublisher="Gesunde Pflanzen" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="197 - 202" refId="B88" refString="Sufyan, M, Abbasi, A, Gogi, MD, Arshad, M, Nawaz, A, Neuhoff, D, 2017. Efficacy of Beauveria bassiana for the management of economically important wireworm species (Coleoptera: Elateridae) in organic farming. Gesunde Pflanzen 69 (4): 197 - 202, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1007/s10343-017-0406-8" title="Efficacy of Beauveria bassiana for the management of economically important wireworm species (Coleoptera: Elateridae) in organic farming." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/s10343-017-0406-8" volume="69" year="2017">Sufyan et al. 2017</bibRefCitation>
); inhabiting soil, plant surfaces and plant internal tissues (
<bibRefCitation id="330595AF5B48B1E8ACB2F210B1C4474B" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.micres.2018.08.016" author="Bamisile, BS" journalOrPublisher="Microbiological Research" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="34 - 50" refId="B2" refString="Bamisile, BS, Dash, CK, Akutse, KS, Keppanan, R, Afolabi, OG, Hussain, M, Qasim, M, Wang, L, 2018. Prospects of endophytic fungal entomopathogens as biocontrol and plant growth promoting agents: an insight on how artificial inoculation methods affect endophytic colonization of host plants. Microbiological Research 217: 34 - 50, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.micres.2018.08.016" title="Prospects of endophytic fungal entomopathogens as biocontrol and plant growth promoting agents: an insight on how artificial inoculation methods affect endophytic colonization of host plants." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.micres.2018.08.016" volume="217" year="2018">Bamisile et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="94B3931862E6F4EDADFB583DBE12CB55" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="DC9EFA531C06B8FE5AC8BDF773F0F34A" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3E7801D0B2D676B5D009C64F87B8B1E5" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Widely distributed.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="BEFC91FDA79B575090ABB8BA4898FCE7" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="notes">
<paragraph id="9957969CAA9D6C8476479DD0ABC59137" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C5049B1F5578B8FBCB0B93D3030B5676" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
<taxonomicName id="80812F264CCB0D434C8A12A60623614D" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Ophiocordycipitaceae" genus="Beauveria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Beauveria bassiana" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="bassiana">
<emphasis id="E02372D8BABAA6E4CEEB0F78D2922C1A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Beauveria bassiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sensu lato includes a large complex of cryptic species with wide host ranges, including many 
<taxonomicName id="BB11A407B5D1284AB379BA337648A1D8" authorityName="Vuillemin" authorityYear="1912" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Ophiocordycipitaceae" genus="Beauveria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="order">Coleoptera</taxonomicName>
families (
<bibRefCitation id="6C1CCC4757E194C1E25A85C2C0A1748F" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3852/10-302" author="Rehner, SA" journalOrPublisher="Mycologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="1055 - 1073" refId="B71" refString="Rehner, SA, Minnis, AM, Sung, GH, Luangsa-ard, JJ, Devotto, L, Humber, RA, 2011. Phylogeny and systematics of the anamorphic, entomopathogenic genus Beauveria. Mycologia 103 (5): 1055 - 1073, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3852/10-302" title="Phylogeny and systematics of the anamorphic, entomopathogenic genus Beauveria." url="https://doi.org/10.3852/10-302" volume="103" year="2011">Rehner et al. 2011</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="06CB4A18DB0078B0C1B4FB02320D4F85" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.aspen.2017.08.015" author="Imoulan, A" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Asia-Pacific Entomology" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="1204 - 1212" refId="B25" refString="Imoulan, A, Hussain, M, Kirk, PM, Meziane, AE, Yao, YJ, 2017. Entomopathogenic fungus Beauveria: host specificity, ecology and significance of morpho-molecular characterization in accurate taxonomic classification. Journal of Asia-Pacific Entomology 20 (4): 1204 - 1212, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.aspen.2017.08.015" title="Entomopathogenic fungus Beauveria: host specificity, ecology and significance of morpho-molecular characterization in accurate taxonomic classification." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.aspen.2017.08.015" volume="20" year="2017">Imoulan et al. 2017</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
